com.intel.fightclub.dialog.coach

Class ArdaAPIHelper

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.intel.fightclub.dialog.coach.ArdaAPIHelper

  • @ThreadSafe
public final class ArdaAPIHelper
extends java.lang.Object
    Utility class to query ARDA's API in the CUI. This class is non-instantiable. Several places need to access ARDA's API, so it's better if all accesses are centralized in one place, instead of each class defining its own methods.

      • getWorkoutType

        @NonNull
 @CheckResult
public static CUIErrorBundle<? extends Queryable> getWorkoutType(@NonNull
                                                                                        android.content.Context context)
        Gets the workout type as a Queryable. The result is not a .PlannedWorkoutTypeCUIWrapper because this query needs to handle cases where the user has chosen to do a free workout. In consequence, this method will first check for the status of the workout choice. If a free workout, we will return "Free". If a planned workout, we will try to get the workout type either from the current workout using QueryInterface or the program for today via ActiveWorkoutDay.
        Parameters:
        context - Application context.
        Returns:
        A CUIErrorBundle containing the workout type, or an ErrorCode indicating what went wrong while getting the data.

 @NonNull

      • getCurrentWorkoutActivity

        @NonNull
 @CheckResult
public static CUIErrorBundle<ActivityCui> getCurrentWorkoutActivity(@NonNull
                                                                                           android.content.Context context)
        Gets the current workout activity, using the behavior specified as part of the .dialog.queries.GetCurrentWorkoutActivity query. This method looks at the current engine state and determines course of action based on it. If in pre workout, the activity will be determined based on user selection. If user selected a plan, then the plan's activity will be returned. If a user selected any type of freeform workout, then the corresponding free activity will result. If in post workout, the activity will be determined based on the most recent completed session. For any other engine states, this method will use the workout retrieved from .queries.GetCurrentWorkout to determine activity.
        Parameters:
        context - Application context, used to retrieve numerous elements from ARDA's api.
        Returns:
        A bundle containing the current activity, or a ErrorCode indicating the reason for not being able to retrieve it.

      • getWorkoutChoiceActivity

        @NonNull
 @CheckResult
public static CUIErrorBundle<ActivityCui> getWorkoutChoiceActivity(@NonNull
                                                                                          android.content.Context context)
        Utility method to determine an activity based on user's workout choice. This method should be used whenever there's a need to determine the activity that the user has currently selected to do. If a free workout has been chosen, then determining the activity is trivial, just determine what type of free workout the user is about to do and return the corresponding activity. If the user wants to follow the plan, then that means that either the activity can be retrieved for the plan or there's no planned workout for the day for any given reason (no program, rest day, etc). If there's no plan, then based on workout choice that implies that the user has not selected a workout.
        Parameters:
        context - Android application context.
        Returns:
        A CUIErrorBundle containing the activity or a ErrorCode if activity could not be retrieved for any reason.
